  "body": "We currently use the beacon-block header HTR hashed against the slot for the skip slot cache key. This requires two calls to hashing routines that are completely unnecessary in in \r\n```go\r\nfunc cacheKey(_ context.Context, state state.ReadOnlyBeaconState) ([32]byte, error) {\r\n\tbh := state.LatestBlockHeader()\r\n\tif bh == nil {\r\n\t\treturn [32]byte{}, errors.New(\"block head in state can't be nil\")\r\n\t}\r\n\tr, err := bh.HashTreeRoot()\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\treturn [32]byte{}, err\r\n\t}\r\n\treturn hash.Hash(append(bytesutil.Bytes32(uint64(state.Slot())), r[:]...)), nil\r\n}\r\n```\r\nWe can simply use the `StateRoot` in `bh` instead of `bh.HashTreeRoot()` and we can just replace the last 8 bytes with the slot instead of hashing. ",
